@Pradagee same thing as last time.  Wait until after 10 to enter..  If the move happens to begin prior, that's fine -- the other 99% of the time it'll be after 10.  Can't win em' all...  
 
Don't let winners turn into losers.  Identify your R/R, then TAKE profits.  Sometimes its 'fun' (and profitable) to let em' run..., but with the volatility lately -- taking profits is the more mature decision.  If you want to test a potential run, then just take a few more contracts (cheap) for that possibility (but don't let the gamble take priority over your job <<<trading to make a living).  
 
In other words:  Be the casino; not the gambler. 
 
You can count on 10 pt pivots (/ES)...all day long.  This translates to 1pt moves on the SPY.  Take advantage.   
 
Remember that VWAP tends to act like an intraday magnet.  So too does the 200ema (1 min chart).  This is especially true for constituent elements of the S&P (like $TSLA, $AAPL, $MSFT, etc)
